Predicates and Sets
A set can be deﬁned using a predicate P
B = {x | P(x)}
B is a set that contains all elements x such that P(x) is true
P(a) = true if and only if a ∈B
Example:
B = {x | x is an even number}
B = {2, 4, 6, 8, . . . }
Example:
C = {(x, y) | x, y ∈N and x + 1 = y}
C = {(1, 2), (2, 3), (3, 4), . . . }
