Consider the following language A
A = {00, 11}
The deﬁnition of start is deﬁned as
A∗= {x1x2 . . . xk | k ≥0 and xi ∈A}
If k = 0, the above deﬁnition becomes
{ | 0 ≥0} = {ε}
If k = 1, the above deﬁnition becomes
{x1 | 1 ≥0 and xi ∈A} = {00, 11}
If k = 2, the above deﬁnition becomes
{x1x2 | 2 ≥0 and xi ∈A} = {0000, 0011, 1100, 1111}
If k = 3, the above deﬁnition becomes
{x1x2x3 | 3 ≥0 and xi ∈A} = {000000, 000011, . . . , 111111}
