Slide 13:
Language of a Method
Consider the following method
boolean N1(String x)
{
boolean p = M(w);
if(p)
return true;
else
return false;
}
In this case, we have no idea about the language of the
method N1()
This is because have no idea what does M(w) return when
called
It may return true
It may return false
It may not return at all (M(w) loops indeﬁnitely)
Thumrongsak Kosiyatrakul tkosiyat@cs.pitt.edu
