Slide 14:
Language of a Method
Suppose M(w) returns true, we can replace M(w) by true as
shown below:
boolean N1(String x)
{
boolean p = true;
// Used to be boolean p = M(w);
if(p)
return true;
else
return false;
}
Now, what is the language of the above method N1?
The language of the method N1 is Σ∗
This is under the assumption that M(w) returns true
So, here is what we can say about the method N1() so far:
If M(w) returns true, the language of N1() is Σ∗
