Slide 16:
Language of a Method
Suppose M(w) does not return at all
It loops indeﬁnitely when called
Since N1() calls M(w) and M(w) loops indeﬁnitely, N1() also
loops indeﬁnitely.
In this case, we can insert the statement while(true); as
shown below
boolean N1(String x)
{
while(true);
// Inserted to make N1 loops indefinitely
boolean p = M(w);
if(p)
return true;
else
return false;
}
Now, what is the language of the above method N1?
Since N1() does not return true on any argument of type
String
The language of the method N1 is ∅
